  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Monitoring and Assessing Current Migrant Flow Profiles in Turkey through the Migrant Presence Monitoring (MPM) Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In line with the objectives of IOM&apos;s Migrant Presence Monitoring (MPM) Programme and in recognition of the continued need for tracking the presence and flow of migrants in Turkey, IOM is proposing to continue data collection activities under this project, in order to provide the Directorate General of Migration Management (DGMM) and service providers in the field of migration access to comprehensive information relating to migration trends, and capacity to sustainably apply the MPM methodology, ultimately contributing to policy making and strategic planning efforts. Under the proposed 12-month project, IOM&apos;s MPM maintains its data collection until the end of November 2021, building on its achievements in establishing the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) and specific MPM methodology in selected provinces of high mobility, and continue publishing reports on the collected data. Reports published will include regular mobility overviews, migration flows, and migrant and refugee demographics, intentions and vulnerabilities in Turkey. IOM implements this project jointly with the Government of Turkey (GoT), thus supporting the GoT to institutionalize valuable data collection structures within the DGMM.</narrative>
  </description>
